examples.en: Pare the rind from the fruit.
The company has to find a way to pare expenses.
Pare off the skin of this fruit very gently, as the flesh is delicate.
This door has swollen in the wet weather and will have to be pared down.
The country's defences have been pared to the bone (=reduced as far as possible).
The firm has not been able to pare costs fast enough to match competitors.
